cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on natural language processing tasks and specifically analyzes the calibration of pre-trained Transformers on three NLP tasks. 
- cs.LG (Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the performance of pre-trained models and their calibration, which is related to machine learning. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with state-of-the-art models in NLP and their performance. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the performance of pre-trained models on a paraphrase detection task, which is related to computer vision. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also less likely but possible as the paper deals with neural models and their calibration.
